                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d159">
                <head>No. 159.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Frelinghuysen</persName> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Denaut</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1883-09-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 22, 1883</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your note of
                    the 12th instant, informing the Department that your Government had determined
                    to reconvene the conference upon the subject of protection to submarine cables,
                    for the purpose of concluding the project of a convention drawn up in November
                    last, and, in recognition of your accompanying request, to signify the
                    concurrence of this Government in the contemplated reunion upon October 15
                    next.</p>
                <p>The delegates of the United States have accordingly been instructed to-day by
                    telegraph to attend the conference and conclude the proposed convention, and
                    that pending the receipt of formal full powers, which will be duly forwarded,
                    they will act upon the authority of their cable instructions.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>FRED’K T. FRELINGHUYSEN.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
